Interface Summary
MiningStack<NodeType,EdgeType> This interface encapsulate the required abilities of stacks to store search nodes for the mining process.
StackList<NodeType,EdgeType> This interface encapsulate the required abilities of a list of stacks.
Strategy<NodeType,EdgeType> This interface encapsulates the requirements of a search strategy.
 

Class Summary
BFSStrategy<NodeType,EdgeType> This class represents a local breadth first extension strategy.
ListItem<Type> This class represents an element of a double linked list
LocalStack<NodeType,EdgeType> This class implements the local part of the dynamic work stealing stack system
RecursiveStrategy<NodeType,EdgeType> This class represents the local recursive strategy.
SMPThread<NodeType,EdgeType> This class represents a single thread for the multi-threaded paralellisation
ThreadedDFSStrategy<NodeType,EdgeType> This class represents the threaded DFS search It is also the head-element of the double linked MiningStack (ring) list and therefore responsible for the work distribution
Worker<NodeType,EdgeType> This class implements the depth-first working for all threads.
 

Package de.parsemis.strategy Description

Contains different strategies for the traversal of a search lattice.

Memorize SearchLatticeNode objects as well as multi-threaded distribution is handled in this package.

The required initial nodes and how to extend them (see the Extender class) depends on the Algorithm.

Author:
Marc Woerlein (woerlein@informatik.uni-erlangen.de)
